          "text": [
            "Processing image: person-322-_jpg.rf.bbc5460ee2c0d5c8cbbd4bcc5248e36d.jpg\n",

      "source": [
        "# Trong qu√° tr√¨nh n√†y s·∫Ω nh·∫≠n bi·∫øt label cho s·∫µn c√≥ thi·∫øu hay sai l·ªách g√¨ hay kh√¥ng\n",
        "import os\n",
        "import random\n",
        "from pathlib import Path\n",
        "from PIL import Image, ImageDraw\n",
        "\n",
        "# Kh·ªüi t·∫°o c√°c class v√† m√†u s·∫Øc cho bounding box\n",
        "classes = [\"head\", \"helmet\", \"person\"]\n",
        "class_colors = {0: \"red\", 1: \"green\", 2: \"blue\"}\n",
        "\n",
        "# tr·∫£ v·ªÅ m·ªôt chu·ªói ƒë·ªãa ch·ªâ images\n",
        "image_folder = \"/content/safety_helmet_dataset/train/images\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# tr·∫£ v·ªÅ m·ªôt chu·ªói ƒë·ªãa ch·ªâ labels\n",
        "label_folder = \"/content/safety_helmet_dataset/train/images\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# ƒê·ªãnh nghƒ©a h√†m v·∫Ω bounding box\n",
        "def draw_boxes(image_path, label_path):\n",
        "    # Open the image\n",
        "    image = Image.open(image_path).convert(\"RGB\")\n",
        "    draw = ImageDraw.Draw(image)\n",
        "    width, height = image.size\n",
        "\n",
        "    if label_path.exists():\n",
        "        with open(label_path, \"r\") as file:\n",
        "            lines = file.readlines()\n",
        "\n",
        "        for line in lines:\n",
        "            # ƒë·ªãnh d·∫°ng YOLO : class_id x_center y_center width height\n",
        "            class_id, x_center, y_center, w, h = map(float, line.strip().split())\n",
        "\n",
        "            x_center *= width\n",
        "            y_center *= height\n",
        "            w *= width\n",
        "            h *= height\n",
        "\n",
        "            x1 = int(x_center - w / 2)\n",
        "            y1 = int(y_center - h / 2)\n",
        "            x2 = int(x_center + w / 2)\n",
        "            y2 = int(y_center + h / 2)\n",
        "\n",
        "            color = class_colors[int(class_id)]\n",
        "\n",
        "            draw.rectangle([x1, y1, x2, y2], outline=color, width=3)\n",
        "            draw.text((x1, y1 - 10), f\"{classes[int(class_id)]}\", fill=color)\n",
        "        display(image)\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(f\"Warning: Label file {label_path} not found.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ch·ªçn ng·∫´u nhi√™n 5 ·∫£nh ƒë·ªÉ v·∫Ω bounding box t·ª´ t·∫≠p train\n",
        "def random_5_train_images(image_folder, label_folder):\n",
        "    image_paths = list(Path(image_folder).glob(\"*.jpg\"))\n",
        "\n",
        "    if len(image_paths) == 0:\n",
        "        print(\"No images found in the specified folder.\")\n",
        "        return\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Tr·ªôn ng·∫´u nhi√™n danh s√°ch c√°c ·∫£nh\n",
        "    random.shuffle(image_paths)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Ch·ªçn 5 ·∫£nh ƒë·∫ßu ti√™n sau khi tr·ªôn\n",
        "    selected_images = image_paths[:5]\n",
        "\n",
        "    # V·∫Ω bounding box cho t·ª´ng ·∫£nh\n",
        "    for image_path in selected_images:\n",
        "        label_path = Path(label_folder) / f\"{image_path.stem}.txt\"\n",
        "        print(f\"Processing image: {image_path.name}\")\n",
        "        draw_boxes(image_path, label_path)\n",
        "\n",
        "# G·ªçi h√†m ƒë·ªÉ v·∫Ω bounding box cho 5 ·∫£nh ng·∫´u nhi√™n\n",
        "random_5_train_images(image_folder, label_folder)\n"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "## Tr·ª±c quan h√≥a s·ª± ph√¢n b·ªë label\n",
        "S·ª≠ d·ª•ng bi·ªÉu ƒë·ªì ƒë·ªÉ ph√¢n t√≠ch, quan s√°t m·∫≠t ƒë·ªô c·ªßa c√°c label"

      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "from collections import defaultdict\n",
        "from pathlib import Path\n",
        "\n",
        "# ƒê∆∞·ªùng d·∫´n t·ªõi th∆∞ m·ª•c ch·ª©a nh√£n\n",
        "label_folder = Path(\"/content/safety_helmet_dataset/train/labels\")  # Thay ƒë∆∞·ªùng d·∫´n th·ª±c t·∫ø\n",
        "\n",
        "# T·∫°o dictionary ƒë·ªÉ ƒë·∫øm s·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng nh√£n theo t·ª´ng lo·∫°i\n",
        "label_counts = defaultdict(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ƒê·ªãnh nghƒ©a t√™n l·ªõp\n",
        "name_class = {\n",
        "              0: \"head\",\n",
        "              1: \"helmet\",\n",
        "              2: \"person\",\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "# Duy·ªát qua t·∫•t c·∫£ file .txt trong th∆∞ m·ª•c labels\n",
        "for label_file in label_folder.glob(\"*.txt\"):\n",
        "    with open(label_file, \"r\") as file:\n",
        "        for line in file:\n",
        "            class_id = int(line.strip().split()[0])  # L·∫•y class_id (d√≤ng ƒë·∫ßu ti√™n trong YOLO format)\n",
        "            label_counts[class_id] += 1  # TƒÉng bi·∫øn ƒë·∫øm cho class_id t∆∞∆°ng ·ª©ng\n",
        "\n",
        "# Chuy·ªÉn dictionary th√†nh 2 danh s√°ch: t√™n l·ªõp v√† s·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng\n",
        "classes = [name_class[class_id] for class_id in label_counts.keys()]\n",
        "counts = list(label_counts.values())\n",
        "\n",
        "# V·∫Ω bi·ªÉu ƒë·ªì c·ªôt b·∫±ng matplotlib & seaborn\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "sns.barplot(x=classes, y=counts, palette='viridis')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Th√™m ti√™u ƒë·ªÅ v√† nh√£n cho c√°c tr·ª•c x, y\n",
        "plt.title(\"S·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng nh√£n theo lo·∫°i trong t·∫≠p Train\", fontsize=16)\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"L·ªõp\", fontsize=12)\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"S·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng\", fontsize=12)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Hi·ªÉn th·ªã bi·ªÉu ƒë·ªì\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
